            <div type="transcript" id="F428A">
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>We grow accustomed to<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 the Dark -</l>
                    <l>When Light is put away - </l>
                    <l>As when the Neighbor holds<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 the Lamp </l>
                    <l>To witness her Good bye - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>A Moment - We uncertain<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 step</l>
                    <l>For newness of the night - </l>
                    <l>Then - fit our Vision to the<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 Dark - </l>
                    <l>And meet the Road - erect - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>And so of larger - Darknesses - </l>
                    <l>Those Evenings of the Brain -</l>
                    <l>When not a Moon disclose<app type="division"><lem><lb/></lem></app>
 a sign - </l>
                    <l>Or Star - come out - within -<app type="division"><lem><pb/></lem></app>
 </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>The <app type="emendation"><lem>Bavest</lem><rdg>Bravest</rdg></app>
 - grope a little - </l>
                    <l>And sometimes hit a Tree </l>
                    <l>Directly in the Forehead -</l>
                    <l>But as they learn to see - </l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Either the Darkness alters - </l>
                    <l>Or something in the sight </l>
                    <l>Adjusts itself to Midnight - </l>
                    <l>And Life steps almost straight.</l>
                </lg>

            </div>     
